##No one knows the danger: The World Dream Luxury cruise ship epidemic

Wechat, boyangcongpeople

The function introduces, peels off the human shell, records the real sensible life. Presented by the in-depth Reporting Department of the Beijing News.

Han did not know at the time that 108 of the thousands of passengers who would spend six days and five nights with her were from Hubei, including 28 from Wuhan.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the 17th floor deck of the World Dream, on January 20. Photo courtesy of the respondents

By Li Yundie, Beijing News

Editor | Wang Jingyi proofread | Fan Jinchun

The text is about 6047 words long and takes about 12 minutes to read

Early in the morning on January 19, a girl from Shaanxi, Han Xin Tong (not her real name) , and her family of five, flew to Guangzhou to begin her "first cruise of my life. ".

They will take the "WD05200119" star Dream cruise-the World Dream" cruise, is the industry's well-known cruise brand, with luxury facilities, rich entertainment and food known, let Han Xin long-awaited. For the trip, the ship will depart from Guangzhou's Nansha port for Vietnam, stop at Nha Trang and Danang, and return to Guangzhou.

At 8 p.m. , passengers began boarding, "especially crowded, all over the country to speak any dialect. ". Han did not know at the time that 108 of the thousands of passengers who would spend six days and five nights with her were from Hubei, including 28 from Wuhan.

January 24, New Year's Eve, "World Dream" returned to Guangzhou, passengers go home. What they took with them, in addition to the happy memories on the cruise ship, was a virus lurking in the bodies of individual passengers.

On February 3, Guangdong CDC issued a notice that several of the newly reported cases of COVID-19 had taken the cruise. Guangdong CDC urged all passengers on the cruise to contact the CDC in the city where they live for immediate reporting and to cooperate with the follow-up work of the CDC staff.

As of February 7, the "World Dream" crew, the new pneumonia has been confirmed cases of seven cases, distributed in Guangdong Zhaoqing, Jiangmen, Guangzhou, Zhuhai, Dongguan, one of which has a family clustering epidemic.

At present, the "World Dream" cruise ship has returned to Hong Kong, in the quarantine work is not completed, without the permission of the HKSAR Department of Health, all passengers and staff can not get off the ship.

Danger undetected

On the day Tong Xin Han arrived in Guangzhou, twenty-five of the last days of the lunar calendar, the winter jasmine flower market in Nansha New Area opened, but a cloud of cold air that day brought scattered drizzle, bringing the temperature that had just rebounded to 19 C. Most of the people on the dock were wearing long-sleeved jackets and padded jackets. Han Xin Tong was still feeling a little cold under her short-sleeved jacket and jeans, which made her feel a little frustrated. "A lot of pretty dresses in the bag didn't come in handy. "

However, after boarding the ship, her depression swept away, "world dream" the luxury of her eye-opener.

According to the official website, the "World Dream" is the second luxury cruise ship under the Hong Kong Xingmeng cruise line. It is 335 meters long and 40 meters wide, with 18 decks and 1,686 rooms, the ship is equipped with duty-free shopping malls, theaters, water slide park and other large-scale recreational shopping facilities.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Six water slides on the world dream. Image: STARDREAM cruises China

Han Tong Xin ran to the canteen that night and ate a big meal. "There are free cafeterias on the 7th, 8th and 16th floors, especially big. So many people ate dinner that night, which is in line with my idea of 'going for a walk' . "

Schefflera Octophylla, 33, and her husband and eldest son from San Kou, Florida, Duanzhou District; mother and daughter, 59, from Dongguan; daughter, 33, from Dalian, Liaoning; resident in Humen; A 65-year-old man and his family from Jinwan District, Zhuhai. Another 108 passengers were from Hubei, 28 of whom were from Wuhan.

They either drive themselves, or travel a long way to Nansha port, boarded the "World Dream" cruise ship, looking forward to the blue sea and blue sky, with their families to greet the arrival of the New Year.

That night, all the passengers boarded the ship, 28-year-old Jiangmen City, the town of Daao Wu Yilin (not his real name) off the ship. According to a later report by the Health Bureau of Jiangmen City, Wu lived alone in a rented house in Panyu District, Guangzhou, and had not been to Wuhan recently. He worked as an Internet salesman and occasionally took a part-time job as a ground attendant on the world dream cruise ship.

On January 19, Wu worked until 9:30 p.m. , an hour and a half after passengers boarded the ship.

However, Han Xin Tong did not have time to pay attention to all this, she and her family soon immersed in the joy of the holiday. They booked two balcony rooms with a view of the sea. During the day, the deck was full of people, "children like to stay in the open-air pool and play on the water slide. Some elderly people in wheelchairs like to sit in the outdoor cinema and watch movies. middle-aged people like to hold the fences and pose for photos. "

The only inconvenience for her was that as the ship moved away from the shore toward the open sea, the cell phone signal dropped off one by one. Finally, "only alipay a software can receive and pay, can send a simple dialogue, even the picture can not send. "

"WI-FI can be bought on board, but it's very expensive, " a crew member told the Beijing News. "It costs 80 yuan for a gigabyte of data, and no one buys it. "

Han Tong Xin and her family didn't buy any. The absence of the Internet did not bother her. Instead, she relished the "idleness" of being "just lying around and eating on a boat. "

The disease is creeping in

Early on the morning of January 21, the world dream arrived in the central Vietnamese city of Nha Trang, where all its passengers spent a day on shore.

Replaced the local Vietnamese mobile phone card, restore the life of the net, Han Xin Tong do the first thing is to brush Weibo. She saw that Weibo was filled with news of academician Zhong Nanshan's statement that "human-to-human transmission has been confirmed" and reports of confirmed and suspected cases of new coronary pneumonia were also being reported outside Hubei Province.

While the "world dream" departure, has been notified of new cases of pneumonia only in Wuhan, experts said the epidemic "can be controlled. Han Tongxin told the Beijing News, "I use Weibo quite a lot, but before the ship to this disease can be said to be completely no concept, do not think with me. "

Seeing the epidemic situation has aggravated trend, Han Tong Xin began to consider, "should wear a mask? "

Nha Trang is not big, Short play period, Han Tong Xin did not find the place to sell the mask. Returning to the world dream in the evening, she found that the only Japanese pharmacy on board had sold out of face masks.

Still, no one on board was wearing a mask. Han Remembers that on the night of January 21, the atmosphere on the deck was still very lively, and the 17th floor swimming pool side Music Party was still in full swing, just like a "large-scale disco scene, " with hundreds of people swaying to the music.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the "World Dream" , the open-air performance area is already crowded with passengers before the night performance begins. Photo courtesy of the respondents

On that day, Wu left his rented house in Guangzhou and went back to his parents'home in the town of Daao, in Jiangmen's Xinhui district, by subway, coach and bus.

Early on the morning of January 22, the world dream arrived in Danang, Vietnam. As soon as we got off the ship, we turned on our cell phones and found that the outbreak was getting worse. The number of confirmed cases of new coronavirus has increased from 291 announced the previous day to 440, with the number of cases and suspected cases increasing in the provinces.

The number of passengers discussing the outbreak has clearly increased. One of the items on the day's trip was a 40-minute supermarket purchase. The passengers all went to buy face masks. Han Xin Tong's mother bought 30.

However, after 8:00 p.m. that night, back on the ship, Han tong-xin noticed that except for a few sporadic passengers, the vast majority of them were still not wearing masks, "maybe everyone thinks it's not that bad, and that pneumonia only exists in the country and the ship is safe for a while. "

The pneumonia situation changed dramatically in a day when the ship continued to sail, again without a network. At 2 am on January 23, Wuhan announced that its city-wide bus, subway, ferry and long-distance passenger services would be suspended from 10 am, and that the airport and railway stations would be temporarily closed from the Han corridor. Zhejiang, Guangdong and Hunan have also started the first-level response to major public health emergencies.

But on the boat, there were no special disinfection measures in those days, said Han Tongxin. "The basic cleaning in the room at ordinary times is to take out the garbage, put toilet paper, and even the carpet in the room has not been vacuumed. "

Soon, the five-to-six-day trip was over. Early on the morning of January 24, the "World Dream" returned to the dock at Nansha port in Guangzhou. Out of the cabin, including Han Xin Tong, including all the passengers have put on a mask, "many of the crew on the ship also put on a mask for the first time. ".

When we got off the ship, the atmosphere was suddenly tense. There were two ambulances parked at the dock, several medical workers in white protective suits walking around, staff sprayed disinfectant on the hands of each passenger and took the temperature of some passengers, "my grandmother was tested at home. " At the time, people felt, "it was really unusual, " Han said

After disembarking, the passengers went home. Ms Jiang's family of three in Zhaoqing, a mother and daughter in Dongguan, a 65-year-old man in Zhuhai and his family all drove home. Han Xin Tong family because of the air ticket, in Guangzhou continued to stay a few days.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Early on the morning of January 24, the "World Dream" arrived in Guangzhou, where two ambulances were parked at the port of Nansha alongside medical staff in white protective suits. Photo courtesy of the respondents

The crew is getting sick

More than one person had been unwell before the ship returned to Nansha port in Guangzhou.

According to previous media reports, Nansha Customs said they had received a report from the ship's doctor that Jiang, from Zhaoqing, had developed fever on January 20. After taking anti-fever medicine, she took a temperature of 37 c the next day and had no fever since then.

On disembarkation, Jiang was screened for new pneumonia but was not considered abnormal at the time. According to a written reply from the Nansha New Area propaganda department in Guangzhou to a reporter from the Beijing News, after the World Dream cruise ship docked on January 24, Nansha customs conducted temperature monitoring and medical inspections on all incoming passengers and crew members, an epidemiological investigation, medical screening and sampling were carried out on 18 passengers with fever present, 7 passengers with fever history during the flight but normal body temperature at the time of entry (including the Zhaoqing Case) , 6 close contacts and key passengers reported by the Shipping Agency, "The results of the night's COVID-19 were negative for nucleic acid. "

However, according to the Zhaoqing Health Bureau, Jiang developed fever again the day after she got off the ship (January 25) , was hospitalized on January 31 and was diagnosed as new crown pneumonia on February 1.

She was not the only passenger to experience discomfort during the flight. The 65-year-old male passenger from Jinwan district, Zhuhai, became ill on January 23, according to the Zhuhai Municipal Health Bureau. It was not clear what specific symptoms he had at the time because of the limited information provided, there's no way to know if he's one of the 31.

After returning home from the world dream, the Zhuhai man apparently did not recover. Two days later, he took a private car to the Red Flag Hospital in Zhuhai, and later to the Golden Bay Hospital, on February 2,120 ambulances were transferred to the Fifth Hospital of Cuhk for isolation treatment. The diagnosis has been confirmed.

Wu Yilin, who returned to his home town of Daao in Jiangmen, also became ill on January 23. According to Jiangmen City Health Bureau later reported, January 23 in the early morning, Wu Yilin began to appear fever, fatigue and other symptoms. He walked to the out-patient clinic of the Daao Health Center that night and has been receiving infusion in the out-patient injection room of the Health Center for the next five days. He was admitted to the single room on the first floor of the Daao Health Center at 8 p.m. on January 28 for treatment, for days without improvement.

He was diagnosed with new coronavirus pneumonia on February 1 and has been transferred to Central Jiangmen Hospital for treatment under isolation.

The briefing provided a detailed account of his eight-day journey from his return home on 21 January to his hospitalization on 28 January. Like countless young people returning home for the Spring Festival, he visited relatives and friends, went to second aunt's home, and had lunch and dinner with second aunt, first cousin and second cousin's family; had dinner with his sister's family of three; and paid New Year's visits to his aunt's home, he chatted with six relatives in a room, partied with friends and fellow villagers, took a friend home on his motorbike and, perhaps unsatisfied with his appearance, went to the SI Qian People's Hospital in the Xinhui district of Jiangmen to have his teeth fixed.

In particular, Wu was not wearing a mask when he was with family, relatives and friends, the circular said.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On February 4, the Health Bureau of Jiangmen City released details of the latest confirmed case of coronary pneumonia, Wu Xlin, who worked part-time as a ground crew on the world dream cruise ship.

According to the results of epidemiological investigations, 21 close contacts of Wu Yilin have been provisionally identified, the Jiangmen Health Bureau reported. At present, all of the 21 close contacts have been contacted by the Health Department of Jiangmen City. Among them, 18 close contacts have been placed under concentrated isolation and observation. Relevant information will be reported to the prevention and Control Headquarters where the remaining 3 close contacts are located for follow-up.

Jiangmen new crown pneumonia prevention and control command, Wu Yi-lin and the same time, contacts with the environment, to the first time the registration of the community, the village, the community or village residents shall report to the Municipal Health Department and keep track of the physical condition of the registrants, or call the local epidemic prevention department to register by telephone and consult the examination and treatment methods, and they shall be isolated at home for observation for 14 days, take your temperature twice a day (in the morning and in the afternoon) .

On February 4, a staff member of the former People's hospital where Wu Yilin went for dental work told the Beijing news that after receiving the news, "The dentists, radiologists and five-sense doctors who have come into contact with him have all tested negative for nucleic acid. He has been here for a short time, 13 days now, and the doctors have no symptoms. "

A Hsinking newspaper reporter called the Daao Health Center, where Wu had been given fluids and hospitalized for nine days before his diagnosis. An official told the Beijing News that during Wu's medical treatment, he developed fever, cough and other symptoms, the hospital also asked him if he had any contact history in Hubei and Wuhan. "He said he had very little contact with people from other places, " the official said. He did not say whether any of the hospital's medical staff had been infected or quarantined.

A village official in Dongsheng village, Daao town, said that the village has been publicizing the prevention and control of the epidemic since January 20, cancelling large-scale activities and informing villagers of the prevention and control of the epidemic through village-wide Radio, electronic screen scrolling prompts and distribution of leaflets.

As for Wu's return, the village official said he knew Wu worked outside the village on weekdays, but did not have his contact details, and it was "unclear" when he would return to the village and leave.

A mother and daughter from Dongguan were also diagnosed after the departure of the world dream. After returning to her home in Humen, the mother developed fever, muscle soreness and other symptoms on January 24, with no apparent improvement after self-medication, while the daughter developed cough symptoms on January 26, according to the Dongguan Municipal Health Bureau. On February 2, two patients were admitted to the city's ninth people's Hospital after isolation treatment, and have been confirmed as new pneumonia.

Ms Jiang's family in Zhaoqing has also been hit by a family cluster. In addition to Jiang, her husband and eldest son, Jiang's mother-in-law, her father-in-law and her 3-year-old son were also diagnosed, according to the Zhaoqing Health Bureau.

Han Xin Tong family is more lucky, more than ten days passed, they did not appear any uncomfortable symptoms.

During her three-or four-day stay in Guangzhou, she saw that the epidemic was being more and more strictly prevented and controlled. The family is on high alert, washing their hands frequently and wearing a mask as soon as they leave their hotel room. When they returned home, they were asked to stay at home and isolate themselves.

On February 7, the Publicity Department of the Nansha District Party Committee in Guangzhou told the Beijing News that the World Dream cruise ship docked on January 24,11 days ago. The incubation period of the virus is 14 days, and the chance of infection among people who have not yet developed the disease is getting smaller and smaller, the masses need not panic excessively, follow the guidance of the professional departments and cooperate actively.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Han Tongxin returned home, still keep the bag on the cruise. Photo courtesy of the respondents

Cruise ship operations suspended

After dropping off passengers from Nansha port in Guangzhou, the "World Dream" returned to Hong Kong. Two days later, on January 26, the General Office of the Ministry of Culture and Tourism issued an "urgent notice on making full efforts to prevent and control the spread of pneumonia caused by COVID-19 infection and suspending the operation of tourism enterprises. " "With immediate effect, travel agencies and online travel companies across the country will suspend the operation of group tours and 'air ticket + hotel' travel products, " it said

The Publicity Department of the Nansha District Party Committee of Guangzhou told the Beijing News that the "World Dream" was originally scheduled to depart from Nansha port on January 26 with more than 3,730 passengers, including about 200 Hubei tourists. After coordination and communication between the relevant departments and the Cruise, the cruise company cancelled the voyage, and the purchase of tickets for tourists to implement a full refund or change of tickets processing.

Star Dream cruises also issued a statement on February 2,2010, in response to the government's measures to contain the spread of the epidemic, suspension of the operation of all its cruises in mainland China and suspension of the movement and turnover of all Chinese staff.

Not only star dream cruises, a check by a reporter from the Beijing News found that a number of cruise companies, including Royal Caribbean cruises and Costa Cruises, have already announced the suspension of some cruises departing from China's home port, and the launch of the corresponding security policy to change the label.

However, even though operations in China's interior have been halted, the world dream is still sailing elsewhere.

Staff Xiao Ai (not her real name) told the Beijing News that at 9 am on January 26, the "World Dream" set off from Hong Kong for the Subic-manila flight on May 6. After a day at sea, the "World Dream" arrived in Manila on January 28. "Most of the tourists got off the ship to play, " it left Manila in the afternoon and returned to Hong Kong on January 31.

At 8 pm that night, the "world dream" immediately began a short weekend tour, more than 8 pm from Hong Kong, stay at sea for a day, February 2 early return to Hong Kong.

In the early morning of February 4, when chatting with a reporter from the Beijing News, Xiao Ai was already on the "Taiwan tour" route. The cruise ship departed Hong Kong on February 2, passing through Geelong, Taiwan and Kaohsiung before returning to Hong Kong on February 5. "When we docked in Port of Kaohsiung on February 4, passengers were not allowed to get off because of the epidemic. We only stopped for a short while and then left, " Xiao said

With the emergence of a number of "world dream"-related confirmed cases, the cruise on the strengthening of prevention and control work. Xiao Ai said that from January 27, the ship carried out disinfection of the ship, suggested that all staff wear masks, daily temperature measurements, to send staff disposable gloves, required to wear when working.

However, Xiao Ai is still a little worried, the ship is crowded, the Casino "many do not wear masks, as well as the elderly. " She is now most afraid of hearing someone cough.

The "World Dream" returned to Hong Kong early on February 5 after a tour of Taiwan. According to a report by Radio Television Hong Kong (RTHK) , staff of the Port Health Division of the HKSAR boarded the vessel for Health Quarantine. All crew members could not leave the vessel without permission from the Department of Health before the quarantine work was completed.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Early on February 5, "World Dream" arrived in Hong Kong, the staff through the ship TV to watch the SAR port health staff on the quarantine of the cruise ship. Photo courtesy of the respondents

Health application forms were collected from more than 1,800 passengers and 1,800 crew members of the vessel for symptom check and temperature screening. According to preliminary information, three of them claimed to have fever but their fever has subsided. One of them tested positive for influenza B. All of them have been sent to public hospitals for isolation and new type pneumonia tests. So far, no results have been released.

Xiao Ai told the Beijing news that in the middle of the night on February 4, the ship called a meeting of the crew and informed them that after all passengers had disembarked after the quarantine was over, the "world dream" would be suspended and all the crew would be quarantined on board. For now, they're still waiting on the boat. "Now, I just want to know if these three people will be diagnosed. "
